The paper discusses adversarial evaluation of natural language understanding models, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-categories. Specifically, the paper focuses on a question answering task called Quizbowl, which involves language understanding, information retrieval, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
